n enrich our understanding of the playwright and his plays.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aChristianity and literaturezEnglandxHistoryy16th century. 0aChristianity and literaturezEnglandxHistoryy17th century. 0aReligion in literature. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aCalvinist.  aCatholicism.  aCrypto-Catholic.  aEnglish.  aKing James I.  aLondon.  aPeter Iver Kaufman.  aQueen Elizabeth I.  aShakespeare.  aStratford-upon-Avon.  aStuart Jacobethan.  aTudor Catholicism.  aTudor puritanism.  areligion.  asecularist.  atheater.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271062495?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271062495423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271062495/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK